      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENSINGTON FLYER (1) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing third (22.95) and beaten 2 lengths over 400m at this track. Comes through a solid form race last start. Top prospect. KATE'S RIFT (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Ballarat over 390m behind Aston Warrior (22.96) in a Grade 5. One of the better hopes. PAW AMARAN (7) has missed the frame at his last two but did run well three back when second (22.92) in a Grade 5 at this track. Well placed here and should do much better. SICILY (8) picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again.",
